Title: Testo 770-2 cable-grab clamp meter
Description: Suitable for non-contact measurements on packed cables with small diameters, the Testo 770-2 clamp meter is designed with a clever retractable pincer-type grab mechanism for operation on hard to work with measuring points, like switching cabinets. With automatic detection and selection of AC/DC and other electrical parameters, such as resistance, continuity, diode and capacitance, as well as starting current, 770-2 provides user-friendly operation with minimal risk of errors. In addition to all the functionality you'll find in the 770-1, this version also includes a temperature adapter and thermocouple probes for the measurement of temperatures as well as electrical parameters.

Title: Testo electrical 745 non-contact voltage tester
Description: Used for quick early checking of suspected faults, the Testo 745 non-contact voltage tester with two-stage sensitivity testing filters high-frequency interference signals. This tester quickly detects voltage or de-energisation, providing indication of voltage through clear visual and acoustic signals. The 745's dual sensitivity stages mean that you're able to detect phase and voltage with one easy to use tool.

Title: Testo Electrical test 750-2 voltage tester
Description: Incorporating an easy to read LED display, the Testo 750-2 voltage tester has large fibre-optic illuminators to indicate the presence of voltage clearly and is additionally suitable for single pole voltage testing to quickly determine whether conductors are live. User-friendly, the 750-2 has a deep-seated anti-slip ring, ergonomic handle and tough housing for comfort and durability. Enabling voltage or de-energization on electrical circuits or systems to be determined, 750-2 is also suitable for continuity testing and rotating magnetic field measurement.
